But how long will it take for them to realise what truly is missing?

A story about being 23, blind dates, and finding who you truly are.

summary: Soooo I know we all pressure Harry to release medicine but can we acknowledge how big a deal it would’ve been for him to even...
body:
Soooo I know we all pressure Harry to release medicine but can we acknowledge how big a deal it would’ve been for him to even get it on the set list?

From being one of the world most sexualised males to standing on a stage and singing about potential gay experiences would’ve been such a vulnerable moment for him.

I imagine it would’ve been a massive battle for him to have that song heard by anybody, let alone as an unrealeased song on a world tour. So while we are all ready for an openly experimental song on his album we all know that Harry will fight for it and we want to be as supportive of his creative rights as possible!

Um.. I checked my dash.
So yeah, either Larry is/was real and they’re really trying to hide that, or Louis’ management has him...
body:
Um.. I checked my dash.

So yeah, either Larry is/was real and they’re really trying to hide that, or Louis’ management has him under deeper closeting than we already think of as “just management.”

Like if they’re making him backtrack on things just because a few tumblr Larries went “lol wouldn’t it be hilarious if…” then Louis is in deep fucking shit (I mean if he is gay, whether Larry was/is real or not, Freddie’s existence takes on like three new possible and very extreme and terrifying insinuations that just DEFINE “deep fucking shit,” but moving on).

Honestly his team must be so fucking thick to think that immediate, obvious as SHIT backtracking would work.

And I mean if you put the jokes aside and really think about it, this shit is just sad. Harry was in a glass closet. Louis is… I don’t even know what you’d call this. Maybe mentioning someone you have a (the biggest) ship (ever) with is some pretty mild shit. Imagine if Liam’s team did this every time he said something that could POSSIBLY tie him to Zayn.

Just.. no.

But still, you have to laugh about it. We’re all so used to this shit now that it’s laugh or have a crisis about what’s really happening and how it all fits and how cruel and sad each new possible answer is.

What’s not to laugh about when there are middle aged men trying to control fangirls?

summary: The Yacht, the eagle tattoo, the perfume commercial, the Another Man wankfest 'interviews' like he'd already made some era...
body:
The Yacht, the eagle tattoo, the perfume commercial, the Another Man wankfest ‘interviews’ like he’d already made some era defining music? Harry was not some soulful indie artist just wanting to put his music out there. He expected mega fame and his whole attitude was like he wanted to shove his power in someone’s face. Given the constant ’*I’m* a good little boy’ sniping interviews I’m gonna guess at least 1 of those people was Zayn (the 'badboy’). He really thought he’d get this mass male audience once he was free from his uncool boyband. They may not have been after top40 radio play but that’s because he was arrogant enough to think he was gonna have some Arctic Monkeys / early KOL type indie success!

The whole thing with that secret london show? He really thought! Harrys been hanging with 'indie’ posers since 2012, he wanted to have theatres full of them and instead he got larries, again.

Indie bands break through because they feed a hunger thats not being fed by top40 in ordinary people (because its always the working class/underclass that creates the scene). HS1 just confirmed what should have been obvious : he doesn’t have the life experience or inner whatever to have anything era defining to say any ordinary yout. He spends so much time now with rich white olds, people who arent just middle aged, they seem like they were born middle aged. The closest thing to youth he gets is the Ks?.

Harry as indierock god is not going to happen so he will go pop. The smarter Harries are already laying the groundwork for it, talking about how ofc HS1 was just so 'their’ type of super perfect edgy experimental rock but they so want him to try 'other genres’. Lol. They know, they’re desperately trying to get their talking points straight for the new direction. He’s Neil Diamond ffs, cheesy cheesy cheese, any decent team would’ve kept his ego in check and maximised his strengths. Men can like warm and soft too yknow, as Louis judging stint is proving.

summary: underneath this grey grey sky | chapter two by nowhere_blake ↳ One Direction | Louis Tomlinson/Harry Styles | 10k words When he...
caption:
underneath this grey grey sky | chapter two by nowhere_blake
↳ One Direction | Louis Tomlinson/Harry Styles | 10k words

When he first hears about Harry, it’s not like in a movie at all. Time doesn’t slow down, there’s no glass shattering to pieces on the floor. It’s fast and almost incomprehensible, the only thing he knows is that he’s more scared and confused than he’s ever been in his whole life.

For a flicker of a moment he thinks it’s a joke, (even though deep down he instinctively already knows, has been feeling it all day, that something’s wrong), ‘What? What do you mean kidnapped?’ he asks back stupidly, and later he won’t even remember who told him, whether it was his assistant, maybe his driver, or someone from management.

It’s all a blur, frantic phone calls, getting on a plane to fly halfway across the world, trying to get it verified that he’s Harry’s next of kin, carding comforting fingers through Gemma’s hair, letting Anne hide the tears in her eyes, pretending he can’t see them, because he knows that she wants to be strong for them.

/ Breaking: One Direction singer Harry Styles found and reunited with family after abducted and held in basement for 5 days /
